<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-01T00:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-01T00:29:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/392</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-01T00:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1917,
                                midnight</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 31, 3 p.m. Direct conflicting reports from <hi rend="italic">Eagle</hi> and Government as to burning of Bartle. Government in
                            telegraphic communication with that point today and report says nothing
                            has occurred there; also commander of two hundred cavalry arriving at
                            Bartle makes no mention of damage. I requested Government to order
                            commander of troops arriving at Manati today to call on Commander <hi rend="italic">Eagle</hi> and furnish information.</p>
                        <p>Federal troops scattered several bands rebels vicinity Manati today
                            killing eighteen.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>